==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Simulate
<hw>Sim"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>simulatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>simulare</ets> to simulate; akin to
<ets>simul</ets> at the same time, together, <ets>similis</ets> like.
See <er>Similar</er>, and cf. <er>Dissemble</er>,
<er>Semblance</er>.]</ety> <def>Feigned; pretended.</def>
<rj><au>Bale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simulate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Simulate
<hw>Sim"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Simulated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Simulating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To assume the mere
appearance of, without the reality; to assume the signs or indications
of, falsely; to counterfeit; to feign.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Puritans, even in the depths of the dungeons to which she had
sent them, prayed, and with no <qex>simulated</qex> fervor, that she
might be kept from the dagger of the assassin.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Simulation</ent>⟦br⟧
